15. Docker Compose (Multi-Container Applications — SRE Perspective)

Most real systems include multiple services.

Application  
Database  
Cache  
Message queue  

Docker Compose allows running distributed systems locally.

Example docker-compose.yml

version: "3.9"

services:
  app:
    image: nginx
    container_name: sre-app
    ports:
      - "8080:80"
    depends_on:
      - redis
    restart: always

  redis:
    image: redis:7
    volumes:
      - redis_data:/data

volumes:
  redis_data:

Run the environment

docker compose up -d
docker compose ps
docker compose logs
docker compose down

Compose prepares engineers for Kubernetes concepts.

Service → Pod  
Network → Cluster networking  
Volumes → Persistent Volumes  

16. Docker Healthchecks (Production Reliability)

In production, SRE teams must detect failing containers automatically.

Docker supports built-in health checks.

Example

HEALTHCHECK --interval=30s --timeout=5s --retries=3 \
 CMD curl -f http://localhost:8080/health || exit 1

This allows Docker to detect:

Application crashes  
Stuck services  
Unresponsive APIs  

Inspect health status

docker inspect --format='{{.State.Health.Status}}' <container>

Why this matters for SRE

Improves self-healing
Detects partial failures
Supports orchestration systems

17. Multi-Stage Builds (Production Optimization)

Multi-stage builds reduce image size and improve security.

Example

FROM node:18 AS builder

WORKDIR /app
COPY . .
RUN npm install
RUN npm run build

FROM node:18-slim

WORKDIR /app
COPY --from=builder /app/dist ./dist

CMD ["node", "dist/app.js"]

Benefits

Smaller images
Faster deployments
Reduced attack surface
Better CI/CD performance

18. Production Docker Compose Example

Example closer to real infrastructure.

version: "3.9"

services:

  web:
    build: .
    ports:
      - "80:8080"
    depends_on:
      - database
      - redis
    restart: always

  database:
    image: postgres:15
    environment:
      POSTGRES_DB: app
      POSTGRES_USER: admin
      POSTGRES_PASSWORD: securepassword
    volumes:
      - db_data:/var/lib/postgresql/data

  redis:
    image: redis:7

volumes:
  db_data:

This architecture is commonly used for:

Internal platforms
Testing production-like systems
Local SRE validation

